                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3697: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-30T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your telegram number 17, February 28, 7 p.m.<note n="95" xml:id="d748fn95"
                        >Not printed.</note> The Foreign Office has learned that the attitude of the
                    Soviets would be that the United States must treat with them directly on the
                    question and <pb facs="0889" n="793" xml:id="pg_793"/> that the Americans are
                    held more or less as hostages. The Czechs will continue their efforts but I do
                    not expect success. There are no new names to report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
